de.greenrobot.event.util

Class ErrorDialogManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.greenrobot.event.util.ErrorDialogManager

  • public class ErrorDialogManager
extends java.lang.Object
    Central class for app that want to use event based error dialogs.

    How to use:
    1. Set the factory to configure dialogs for your app, typically in Application#onCreate()
    2. Use one of attachTo(Activity), attachTo(Activity, boolean) or attachTo(Activity, boolean, Bundle) in your Activity, typically in onCreate.
    For more complex mappings, you can supply your own ErrorDialogFragmentFactory.
